  <h3 class="pg-h">What is Botox and how does it work?</h3>
  <p class="pg-text">Botox is an FDA-approved injectable treatment made from a purified protein that temporarily relaxes the facial muscles responsible for wrinkles. It works by blocking nerve signals to specific muscles, preventing them from contracting and forming lines. When skillfully administered by Dr. Menon at our Millburn clinic, Botox reduces the appearance of forehead lines, crow's feet, frown lines, and other facial wrinkles without affecting your ability to make natural expressions. The treatment effectively addresses dynamic wrinkles (those caused by repeated facial movements) and can prevent deeper static wrinkles from forming over time. Dr. Menon's medical expertise ensures precise placement for optimal results, targeting only the muscles that contribute to unwanted lines while preserving your natural facial mobility.</p>
